# Charts: use Recharts

`recharts` is the standard charting library for this frontend. Use it for any
data visualization (line, area, bar, pie/donut, composed, scatter).

- Do NOT add other chart libraries (chart.js, react-chartjs-2, ApexCharts, nivo, victory, d3 for charts).
- Always wrap charts in `<ResponsiveContainer>` and give the parent a fixed height.
- Format value axes/tooltips with the tenant currency via `formatMoney`.
- Use theme colors (`useTheme().palette.*`) for strokes/fills where possible.
- A single-value progress/gauge can stay as MUI `LinearProgress`; multi-point
  series and category comparisons should be Recharts.

```jsx
import {
  AreaChart, Area, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip, ResponsiveContainer,
} from 'recharts';

<Box sx={{ width: '100%', height: 300 }}>
  <ResponsiveContainer>
    <AreaChart data={data}>
      <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" />
      <XAxis dataKey="period" />
      <YAxis tickFormatter={(v) => formatMoney(v)} />
      <Tooltip formatter={(v) => formatMoney(v)} />
      <Area type="monotone" dataKey="revenue" strokeWidth={2} />
    </AreaChart>
  </ResponsiveContainer>
</Box>
```

Reference implementations: `frontend/src/pages/business/dashboard/components/SalesAnalyticsSection.jsx`,
`frontend/src/pages/business/expenses/components/ExpenseCharts.jsx`.
